I tried to write her a couple of times.

101
00:06:21,128 --> 00:06:23,411
But to be fair, my address changed.

102
00:06:23,462 --> 00:06:25,926
I had a lot going on in my life then, too.

103
00:06:27,419 --> 00:06:28,596
College...

104
00:06:32,952 --> 00:06:34,286
...and then you.

105
00:06:34,804 --> 00:06:35,560
Me?

106
00:06:36,080 --> 00:06:39,338
My very own Boy Scout Jamboree.

107
00:06:56,022 --> 00:06:59,192
Allison, I'd like you to meet Councilman Stuart McCallister.

108
00:07:05,455 --> 00:07:07,661
The Councilman has come to me with a personal problem,

109
00:07:07,712 --> 00:07:11,066
and Detective Scanlon and I thought you might be able to help.

110
00:07:11,496 --> 00:07:13,604
I'm, uh, trying to locate someone,

111
00:07:14,225 --> 00:07:18,032
and I'm told that you're, uh, pretty good at that.

112
00:07:18,801 --> 00:07:20,225
Well, I have my days.

113
00:07:20,765 --> 00:07:22,391
So, who are you looking for?

114
00:07:22,870 --> 00:07:23,653
My daughter.

115
00:07:24,222 --> 00:07:25,837
He hasn't seen her for a week.

116
00:07:25,888 --> 00:07:28,465
She said she was going to a movie and never came home.

117
00:07:28,516 --> 00:07:29,521
I'm so sorry.

118
00:07:30,255 --> 00:07:31,713
It's not the first time.

119
00:07:32,566 --> 00:07:34,222
She's 19, and the truth is,

120
00:07:34,273 --> 00:07:37,839
