243
00:14:51,489 --> 00:14:53,219
Dirty Little Darlings IV?

244
00:14:53,575 --> 00:14:54,331
Pardon?

245
00:14:54,590 --> 00:14:56,280
It's the title of the movie that she's in.

246
00:14:56,331 --> 00:14:57,831
He was trying to find it.

247
00:14:58,093 --> 00:15:01,245
The other day when I saw into his head, I misunderstood.

248
00:15:02,631 --> 00:15:04,953
I think he was trying to find this movie.

249
00:15:05,666 --> 00:15:07,938
I think he's having trouble believing it.

250
00:15:10,547 --> 00:15:11,695
How you holding up?

251
00:15:12,546 --> 00:15:14,784
You know what?
I'll take it from here.

252
00:15:15,074 --> 00:15:16,451
What are you talking about?

253
00:15:16,502 --> 00:15:18,350
I'm going to drop you off at your house.

254
00:15:18,401 --> 00:15:22,065
You need to be by yourself, get upset, say good bye to your friend.

255
00:15:22,336 --> 00:15:23,786
You are entitled to that.

256
00:15:29,670 --> 00:15:31,244
I can't believe she's doing this.

257
00:15:31,295 --> 00:15:33,722
This? How about going to California?

258
00:15:34,387 --> 00:15:35,793
Should we tell somebody?

259
00:15:36,355 --> 00:15:38,155
Who are we going to tell?
Her mother?

260
00:15:38,206 --> 00:15:39,644
Her mother's not going to care.

261
00:15:39,695 --> 00:15:40,985
We can't let her go.

262
00:15:44,391 --> 00:15:45,339
Thank you.

263
00:15:52,195 --> 00:15:54,578
Okay, so if anyone asks, my name's Linda.

264
00:15:54,887 --> 00:15:56,663
I'm a junior at the U. of A.

265
00:15:57,099 --> 00:15:59,374
And you girls are my dorm mates.

266
00:16:05,464 --> 00:16:08,097
Ally, what you looking at?
The boys are over there.

267
00:16:08,148 --> 00:16:09,043
Sorry.

268
00:16:11,003 --> 00:16:13,879
Lyla, I'm worried about you, worried about this plan.

269
00:16:14,341 --> 00:16:16,923
Don't worry about it.
I got it under control.

270
00:16:25,249 --> 00:16:26,290
You okay?

271
00:16:26,855 --> 00:16:28,833
You look like you've seen a ghost.

272
00:16:31,236 --> 00:16:32,404
Tell me something.

273
00:16:33,480 --> 00:16:35,114
What's it like to be drunk?

274
00:16:36,135 --> 00:16:37,556
Uh, what do you mean?

275
00:16:38,363 --> 00:16:39,415
What's it like?

276
00:16:40,861 --> 00:16:42,411
It's like what it's like.

277
00:16:42,715 --> 00:16:43,695
You want a sip?

278
00:16:45,527 --> 00:16:46,852
I don't know.

279
00:16:48,028 --> 00:16:49,316
A toast to me.

280
00:16:49,694 --> 00:16:50,643
New beginnings.

281
00:17:03,512 --> 00:17:07,050
You stay in there any longer, you're going to turn into a prune.

282
00:17:07,948 --> 00:17:10,360
A beautiful, naked prune.

283
00:17:13,971 --> 00:17:16,251
How could I not have known she was dead?

284
00:17:16,870 --> 00:17:19,115
I don't know.
You told me her family life was a mess.

285
00:17:19,166 --> 00:17:21,748
It wasn't like they were going to contact you.

286
00:17:22,536 --> 00:17:23,726
You were in college.

287
00:17:23,861 --> 00:17:26,561
You probably weren't reading the papers every day.

288
00:17:27,259 --> 00:17:28,207
It was years ago.

289
00:17:28,258 --> 00:17:29,540
I'm talking about me.

290
00:17:30,413 --> 00:17:34,292
I see the dead. They send me messages.
I'm the one they all come to.

291
00:17:36,029 --> 00:17:37,793
How could I not have known?

292
00:17:58,444 --> 00:17:59,466
What's going on?

293
00:17:59,884 --> 00:18:02,148
They just found Cynthia McCallister's car.

294
00:18:07,534 --> 00:18:09,600
More blood in that car than...

295
00:18:12,319 --> 00:18:14,410
If it all turns out to belong to Cynthia McCallister,

296
00:18:14,461 --> 00:18:18,190
we're going to need to upgrade her from missing teen to homicide victim.

297
00:18:18,241 --> 00:18:21,385
I better put in a call to the Councilman, make him aware.

298
00:18:21,440 --> 00:18:22,504
Where's the body?

299
00:18:22,945 --> 00:18:23,841
I don't know.

300
00:18:25,289 --> 00:18:27,527
I was kind of hoping you could tell me.

301
00:19:02,955 --> 00:19:04,478
I can barely see you.

302
00:19:06,862 --> 00:19:08,266
I can't hear you.

303
00:19:10,127 --> 00:19:12,462
Go find someone else!

304
00:19:13,658 --> 00:19:15,132
Leave me alone!

305
00:19:15,639 --> 00:19:18,510
Shut up!
Go away! I can't hear you!

306
00:19:40,546 --> 00:19:42,130
Well, aren't you the sight.

307
00:19:49,412 --> 00:19:54,249
Katie and Suzannah just took off, so... I guess it's just you and me.

308
00:19:56,296 --> 00:19:57,886
Hey, you okay?

309
00:19:59,389 --> 00:20:00,420
I'm excellent.

310
00:20:02,200 --> 00:20:05,402
I'm actually... excellent.

311
00:20:13,791 --> 00:20:14,897
Got to tell you...

312
00:20:15,801 --> 00:20:19,247
this is not where I expected to spend my last night in Phoenix.

313
00:20:24,190 --> 00:20:25,353
Then don't go.

314
00:20:27,051 --> 00:20:28,052
I got to go.

315
00:20:30,953 --> 00:20:34,243
I'm going to miss you so much.

316
00:20:37,171 --> 00:20:38,174
Me, too.

317
00:21:04,158 --> 00:21:04,953
Anything?

318
00:21:06,651 --> 00:21:08,149
Not about this, no.

319
00:21:09,940 --> 00:21:11,960
I could take you back to the house.

320
00:21:12,258 --> 00:21:15,720
Well, I'm sure I could be just as useless there as I am here.

321
00:21:18,569 --> 00:21:19,213
Okay.

322
00:21:19,287 --> 00:21:21,039
These things were in her car...

323
00:21:22,954 --> 00:21:24,496
the place where she was murdered.

324
00:21:24,547 --> 00:21:27,797
She touched them. They surrounded her,
probably at the moment of her death.

325
00:21:27,848 --> 00:21:32,257
There should be... some kind of energy to these things--

326
00:21:32,523 --> 00:21:35,433
her energy.
They should tell me something about her...

327
00:21:36,552 --> 00:21:38,212
about her last moments, but...

328
00:21:38,628 --> 00:21:40,162
when I hold these things...

329
00:21:42,846 --> 00:21:45,991
Look. I don't mean to pour salt in the wound.

330
00:21:48,223 --> 00:21:51,325
I watched, uh, Dirty Little Darlings IV last night.

331
00:21:52,975 --> 00:21:54,160
Twice actually.

332
00:21:55,231 --> 00:21:56,379
I'm sorry, Allison.

333
00:21:57,125 --> 00:21:59,473
Cynthia McCallister's nowhere in that movie.

334
00:22:00,636 --> 00:22:01,552
Of course not.

335
00:22:05,513 --> 00:22:07,122
Just hung up with Forensics.

336
00:22:07,340 --> 00:22:10,432
Preliminary tests indicate that all the blood in the car is Cynthia's--

337
00:22:10,483 --> 00:22:12,019
over four liters of the stuff.

338
00:22:12,070 --> 00:22:15,201
There's simply no way she would have survived without an immediate transfusion.

339
00:22:15,252 --> 00:22:17,671
We've checked every hospital in the state-- nothing.

340
00:22:17,722 --> 00:22:18,798
So where does that leave us?

341
00:22:18,849 --> 00:22:21,515
We need to find her body or a weapon, something.

342
00:22:21,672 --> 00:22:23,492
Doesn't do us any good to find the man that killed her

343
00:22:23,543 --> 00:22:25,423
if we can't prove it in a court of law.

344
00:22:25,474 --> 00:22:26,622
The Councilman's office just called.

345
00:22:26,673 --> 00:22:28,299
He's ready whenever you are.

346
00:22:28,688 --> 00:22:30,697
The Councilman agreed to take a polygraph.

347
00:22:30,748 --> 00:22:33,539
You asked the grieving father to take a lie detector test?

348
00:22:33,590 --> 00:22:34,887
It's standard procedure.

349
00:22:34,938 --> 00:22:37,730
He understands that the sooner we can rule out family members, boyfriends,

350
00:22:37,781 --> 00:22:40,265
anyone else around Cynthia that might be considered a suspect,

351
00:22:40,316 --> 00:22:44,870
the sooner we can concentrate our efforts on finding the person that actually did this.

352
00:22:46,166 --> 00:22:47,700
Have you ever stolen money?

353
00:22:49,531 --> 00:22:50,200
No.

354
00:22:51,805 --> 00:22:53,572
Is your name Stuart McCallister?

355
00:22:54,556 --> 00:22:55,371
Yes.

356
00:22:56,804 --> 00:23:00,108
Do you have any knowledge of the whereabouts of your daughter?

357
00:23:01,606 --> 00:23:02,454
No.

358
00:23:03,910 --> 00:23:06,006
Is your daughter's name Cynthia Marie?

359
00:23:07,591 --> 00:23:08,306
Yes.

360
00:23:11,061 --> 00:23:13,467
Did you have anything to do with her death?

361
00:23:19,606 --> 00:23:22,314
Did you have anything to do with Cynthia's death?

362
00:23:24,679 --> 00:23:26,837
No, I did not.

363
00:23:27,969 --> 00:23:29,017
Nothing whatsoever?

364
00:23:30,726 --> 00:23:32,282
Nothing whatsoever.

365
00:24:07,145 --> 00:24:08,365
Daddy, don't.

366
00:24:13,805 --> 00:24:14,861
Is today Thursday?

367
00:24:15,943 --> 00:24:16,985
Yes, it is.

368
00:24:18,496 --> 00:24:20,741
Is your name Stuart McCallister?

369
00:24:21,538 --> 00:24:22,394
Yes, it is.

370
00:24:45,529 --> 00:24:46,450
Stuart?

371
00:24:50,074 --> 00:24:51,054
Manuel.

372
00:24:54,680 --> 00:24:57,107
It's 9:30 at night, Manuel, we're meeting in the dark.

373
00:24:57,158 --> 00:24:59,698
I'm assuming you've found my daughter's body.

374
00:24:59,837 --> 00:25:02,209
What's left of it.
Do me the courtesy of

375
00:25:02,567 --> 00:25:05,485
telling me quickly.
I'm not keen on theatrics.

376
00:25:05,668 --> 00:25:09,164
We've not found your daughter, that's not why I asked you here.

377
00:25:09,456 --> 00:25:10,208
Sit.

378
00:25:10,870 --> 00:25:11,814
I'm fine.

379
00:25:14,357 --> 00:25:16,839
What are we doing here, Mr. District Attorney?

380
00:25:18,117 --> 00:25:20,137
I've known you a long time, Stuart.

381
00:25:20,721 --> 00:25:23,705
You're speaking of me as if I were the one who died.

382
00:25:25,070 --> 00:25:28,190
One of my investigators has shared with me a certain...

383
00:25:28,669 --> 00:25:29,900
theory of evidence.

384
00:25:31,121 --> 00:25:35,224
Before I commit further resources,
brief other investigators, ask...

385
00:25:35,572 --> 00:25:39,667
others to follow this lead and thereby
make it a matter of public record,

386
00:25:40,626 --> 00:25:44,106
I wanted to give you the opportunity to speak to its... veracity.

387
00:25:44,904 --> 00:25:45,834
Off the record.

388
00:25:46,513 --> 00:25:48,751
I don't know what you're talking about.

389
00:25:51,804 --> 00:25:52,961
I need to know,

390
00:25:53,327 --> 00:25:56,890
is there anything about the nature of your relationship with your daughter

391
00:25:56,941 --> 00:25:59,398
that might be seen as unique or special?

392
00:26:21,099 --> 00:26:22,071
They called you?

393
00:26:25,680 --> 00:26:26,946
They contacted you?

394
00:26:29,619 --> 00:26:30,580
I'm sorry?

395
00:26:30,797 --> 00:26:33,689
She'd been gone two days when I got the first call.

396
00:26:33,999 --> 00:26:36,001
They sent me to one of those...

397
00:26:37,377 --> 00:26:38,774
adult movie stores.

398
00:26:38,977 --> 00:26:40,152
Video stores.

399
00:26:40,808 --> 00:26:42,705
Told me to buy this used DVD...

400
00:26:44,541 --> 00:26:45,389
and watch it.

401
00:26:47,236 --> 00:26:48,905
They wanted $100,000.

402
00:27:02,465 --> 00:27:03,839
And I sent it to them.

403
00:27:07,608 --> 00:27:09,352
And they slaughtered her anyway.

404
00:27:10,464 --> 00:27:11,357
I'm sorry...

405
00:27:12,564 --> 00:27:13,247
I'm lost.

406
00:27:13,298 --> 00:27:15,103
Are you telling me your daughter was kidnapped?

407
00:27:15,154 --> 00:27:17,556
I'm telling you the same thing I told you the first time I came in here--

408
00:27:17,607 --> 00:27:20,457
that my daughter consorted with unsavory people.

409
00:27:21,232 --> 00:27:23,576
And I believe these people are the ones who killed her...

410
00:27:23,627 --> 00:27:27,719
the ones who tricked her into taping us,
the ones who were blackmailing me.

411
00:27:29,031 --> 00:27:33,125
So you're telling me that there's some sort of recording out there?

412
00:27:34,444 --> 00:27:36,806
And that it... documents...

413
00:27:37,247 --> 00:27:39,201
your relationship with your daughter?

414
00:27:41,776 --> 00:27:43,992
I thought we were going to be direct
and honest with each other, Manuel.

415
00:27:44,043 --> 00:27:45,551
Don't get coy on me now.

416
00:27:52,618 --> 00:27:53,649
You're shocked.

417
00:27:54,709 --> 00:27:56,899
My feelings are beside the point, Stuart.

418
00:27:56,950 --> 00:27:59,128
I'm a civilized person, Manuel.

419
00:28:01,561 --> 00:28:03,187
I know what you're thinking.

420
00:28:04,018 --> 00:28:05,011
But I am not...

421
00:28:06,092 --> 00:28:09,239
- the author of this situation.
- You were the parent.

422
00:28:12,809 --> 00:28:14,584
When Cynthia's mother died...

423
00:28:16,575 --> 00:28:17,908
I realized...

424
00:28:20,789 --> 00:28:23,818
giving comfort to an 11-year-old girl...

425
00:28:25,138 --> 00:28:25,875
it's...

426
00:28:28,811 --> 00:28:29,996
it's not really...

427
00:28:32,227 --> 00:28:33,811
something I knew how to do.

428
00:28:37,595 --> 00:28:38,336
But...

429
00:28:40,440 --> 00:28:44,072
she was in such distress.

430
00:28:44,134 --> 00:28:46,054
Did you kill your daughter, Stuart?

431
00:28:49,269 --> 00:28:50,260
Of course not.

432
00:28:55,305 --> 00:28:56,651
I loved my daughter.

433
00:29:13,712 --> 00:29:16,010
Councilman McCallister, where are you going?

434
00:29:17,375 --> 00:29:18,051
Home.

435
00:29:20,431 --> 00:29:21,305
To grieve.

436
00:29:21,661 --> 00:29:24,471
Sir, I don't think I can let you leave.

437
00:29:28,832 --> 00:29:30,726
I don't think you have a choice.

438
00:29:32,626 --> 00:29:35,636
This is America--
you can't charge a man with hearsay.

439
00:29:38,276 --> 00:29:40,115
Good night, Mr. District Attorney.

440
00:30:04,947 --> 00:30:05,979
It's your boss.

441
00:30:06,851 --> 00:30:08,737
He was just here.
We just spoke.

442
00:30:09,403 --> 00:30:11,189
Everything you suspected is true.

443
00:30:14,353 --> 00:30:15,933
So what happens now?

444
00:30:16,204 --> 00:30:17,344
Nothing happens now.

445
00:30:17,455 --> 00:30:19,601
I can't offer your vision as evidence.

446
00:30:20,534 --> 00:30:23,418
And unless and until that DVD surfaces...

447
00:30:26,478 --> 00:30:27,339
I got to go.

448
00:30:27,700 --> 00:30:28,504
I understand.

449
00:30:32,279 --> 00:30:34,015
And the punch line is:

450
00:30:35,424 --> 00:30:36,844
life sucks.

451
00:30:42,881 --> 00:30:44,146
And the joke is?

452
00:30:46,533 --> 00:30:47,731
It's what you said?

453
00:30:49,810 --> 00:30:50,971
His own daughter.

454
00:30:55,285 --> 00:30:56,345
I'm sorry.

455
00:30:56,782 --> 00:30:58,852
And he's going to get away with it.

456
00:31:02,265 --> 00:31:03,390
Why?

457
00:31:05,192 --> 00:31:07,665
Why fill my head with all this ugliness

458
00:31:08,392 --> 00:31:11,368
when it doesn't matter,
when it doesn't do any good?

459
00:31:13,943 --> 00:31:16,031
Why wouldn't Lyla visit me?

460
00:31:17,418 --> 00:31:20,176
Why wouldn't she tell me herself that she's gone?

461
00:31:23,877 --> 00:31:25,113
I don't know, baby.

462
00:31:37,673 --> 00:31:38,354
Joe?

463
00:31:38,559 --> 00:31:39,551
Joe?

464
00:31:40,161 --> 00:31:41,390
Joe? Joe?

465
00:31:42,415 --> 00:31:43,024
Joe!

466
00:31:43,617 --> 00:31:45,439
What?! What?!
What is it?

467
00:31:45,611 --> 00:31:48,319
We just had an earthquake.
Didn't you feel that?

468
00:31:48,907 --> 00:31:49,729
No.

469
00:31:50,039 --> 00:31:52,059
All I feel is you shaking me awake.

470
00:31:53,033 --> 00:31:54,449
I don't hear the girls.

471
00:31:55,111 --> 00:31:56,677
I don't hear any sirens.

472
00:31:57,318 --> 00:31:59,354
- I'm telling you, we had an earthquake.
- Power's on.

473
00:31:59,405 --> 00:32:01,700
I've been dreaming about it for days and we finally had one.

474
00:32:01,751 --> 00:32:04,882
I had a glass of water on the bedside table beside me and it's filled to the top.

475
00:32:04,933 --> 00:32:06,257
Not a drop is missing.

476
00:32:06,783 --> 00:32:09,301
Fine, don't believe me.
I'm putting on the news.

477
00:32:09,352 --> 00:32:10,479
Excuse me?

478
00:32:10,546 --> 00:32:12,576
You'll see.
It'll be on the news.

479
00:32:14,648 --> 00:32:17,508
And in the small Arizona border town of San Miguel,

480
00:32:17,559 --> 00:32:22,488
residents are applauding the selfless actions of local teacher, Geraldine Hanscom.

481
00:32:22,795 --> 00:32:23,632
Earlier this week,

482
00:32:23,683 --> 00:32:28,418
the very shy Ms. Hanscom not only risked her life to save a young girl from drowning,

483
00:32:28,696 --> 00:32:30,596
They're going to put one of those little banners across the bottom.

484
00:32:30,647 --> 00:32:33,783
but actually turned down a generous cash reward offered to her by the girl's parents.

485
00:32:33,834 --> 00:32:34,434
Instead,

486
00:32:34,456 --> 00:32:38,815
Ms. Hanscom asked that the money be donated to the local San Miguel High School

487
00:32:38,991 --> 00:32:42,057
where she teaches English to teenage migrant workers.

488
00:32:42,681 --> 00:32:43,403
Three days ago,

489
00:32:43,454 --> 00:32:46,933
Ms. Hanscom nearly lost her own life while rescuing a young girl

490
00:32:46,984 --> 00:32:49,444
who had fallen into a flash-flooded river.

491
00:32:49,637 --> 00:32:52,337
Floods don't count, we're looking for earthquakes.

492
00:32:53,315 --> 00:32:54,039
Ow.

493
00:32:55,674 --> 00:32:56,479
It's her.

494
00:32:57,597 --> 00:32:58,799
Joe, it's Lyla.

495
00:32:59,503 --> 00:33:01,305
That's her.
She's still alive.

496
00:33:01,626 --> 00:33:02,728
Lyla Gallagher?

497
00:33:03,884 --> 00:33:05,173
How's that possible?

498
00:33:05,491 --> 00:33:06,433
I don't know.

499
00:33:07,810 --> 00:33:10,668
But when I get a chance, I'm going to go ask her.

500
00:33:15,738 --> 00:33:18,354
You're trespassing, and I will call the sheriff.

501
00:33:18,731 --> 00:33:19,967
How do I get you people to understand

502
00:33:20,018 --> 00:33:22,704
I have no interest in being in the paper or on television.

503
00:33:22,755 --> 00:33:25,008
Lyla, it's me.

504
00:33:25,059 --> 00:33:27,040
It's Allison.
It's Allison Rolen.

505
00:33:30,867 --> 00:33:32,443
Oh, my God. Allison.

506
00:33:37,119 --> 00:33:38,111
Oh, crap.

507
00:33:45,198 --> 00:33:46,430
They're so beautiful.

508
00:33:47,949 --> 00:33:49,051
What about you?

509
00:33:50,292 --> 00:33:54,711
I have 23 of them, and they'll be here in about ten minutes.

510
00:33:55,709 --> 00:33:57,182
I saw you on television.

511
00:33:57,233 --> 00:34:00,864
Well, I saw Geraldine Hanscom on television.

512
00:34:01,999 --> 00:34:03,323
I was looking for you.

513
00:34:05,945 --> 00:34:06,669
Okay.

514
00:34:11,076 --> 00:34:12,526
It's flattering, I guess.

515
00:34:17,495 --> 00:34:19,431
But I need you to leave me alone.

516
00:34:20,488 --> 00:34:21,297
What?

517
00:34:22,517 --> 00:34:23,491
Why?

518
00:34:23,571 --> 00:34:26,832
Lyla... the whole world thinks you're dead.

519
00:34:27,008 --> 00:34:31,817
I know, and it took a lot of time, luck and money to make it happen.

520
00:34:34,857 --> 00:34:36,735
So, please, Allison, just go home.

521
00:34:36,992 --> 00:34:38,394
Not without a why.

522
00:34:39,717 --> 00:34:41,504
Not without an answer.

523
00:34:42,224 --> 00:34:44,187
I drove all night to get here.

524
00:34:44,325 --> 00:34:46,169
I'm not going home empty-handed.

525
00:34:49,671 --> 00:34:51,079
You ever made a mistake?

526
00:34:52,928 --> 00:34:56,508
When I left Phoenix and came to California, I made a lot of them.

527
00:34:56,794 --> 00:34:58,378
I even married one of them.

528
00:34:59,953 --> 00:35:03,701
Did a lot of really stupid things with a lot of really stupid people.

529
00:35:04,316 --> 00:35:05,575
Did a lot for money.

530
00:35:07,282 --> 00:35:09,269
Took a lot of really stupid drugs.

531
00:35:10,384 --> 00:35:12,396
Made a lot of really stupid choices.

532
00:35:13,528 --> 00:35:14,936
It just got really dark.

533
00:35:17,163 --> 00:35:18,965
The truth is I wanted to die...

534
00:35:20,676 --> 00:35:25,542
and I realize now I did everything short of actually killing myself to make it happen.

535
00:35:27,239 --> 00:35:29,343
My husband Billy and I were up north.

536
00:35:30,236 --> 00:35:31,980
We were driving through Oakland.

537
00:35:32,217 --> 00:35:34,419
We got into this enormous fight--
something about drugs.

538
00:35:34,470 --> 00:35:36,335
I took his, he took mine.

539
00:35:37,427 --> 00:35:41,221
We needed money, and I was in no shape to do what was necessary to get it.

540
00:35:41,272 --> 00:35:44,024
Anyway, he throws me out of his car.

541
00:35:44,351 --> 00:35:47,387
I mean, I'm in the middle of Oakland with nothing.

542
00:35:50,622 --> 00:35:53,057
It's October 17, 1989.

543
00:35:54,724 --> 00:35:56,904
20 minutes later, the whole place shook.

544
00:35:57,649 --> 00:35:59,200
It was a 7.1 earthquake.

545
00:35:59,759 --> 00:36:00,757
I remember it.

546
00:36:01,575 --> 00:36:02,672
I read about it.

547
00:36:02,939 --> 00:36:04,549
Me, too, the next day.

548
00:36:06,189 --> 00:36:07,513
I was in this shelter.

549
00:36:08,789 --> 00:36:10,157
I saw this paper.

550
00:36:10,482 --> 00:36:12,116
There's a list of the dead.

551
00:36:13,043 --> 00:36:14,761
Me and my husband were on it.

552
00:36:16,083 --> 00:36:19,227
My wallet, my bag, everything I owned was in Billy's car.

553
00:36:19,645 --> 00:36:22,957
Billy's car went off the Oakland Bay Bridge during the quake.

554
00:36:23,249 --> 00:36:24,208
Oh, my God.

555
00:36:24,623 --> 00:36:26,249
At first, I was frantic.

556
00:36:27,116 --> 00:36:28,694
Everyone thinks I'm dead.

557
00:36:29,275 --> 00:36:30,439
This is horrible.

558
00:36:33,496 --> 00:36:35,014
But then I realized...

559
00:36:36,633 --> 00:36:37,567
no.

560
00:36:39,131 --> 00:36:41,017
This is the chance of a lifetime.

561
00:36:42,432 --> 00:36:44,662
This is the chance of a second lifetime.

562
00:36:44,975 --> 00:36:47,095
I don't get it.
How did you do it?

563
00:36:47,340 --> 00:36:51,274
A new name?
A new social security number?

564
00:36:53,969 --> 00:36:55,033
There's this guy.

565
00:36:55,273 --> 00:36:56,379
His name's Sammy.

566
00:36:56,490 --> 00:36:58,468
He works out of a room in Nogales.

567
00:36:59,221 --> 00:37:01,107
He can get you anything you need.

568
00:37:01,162 --> 00:37:02,557
The ultimate do-over.

569
00:37:04,254 --> 00:37:06,781
The only thing is it costs $100,000.

570
00:37:08,276 --> 00:37:10,716
Took me five years to work it off.

571
00:37:12,551 --> 00:37:16,018
I answered phones.

572
00:37:16,554 --> 00:37:18,002
I made deliveries.

573
00:37:18,443 --> 00:37:20,447
Got my teaching certificate at night.

574
00:37:23,705 --> 00:37:25,373
But I would've done anything.

575
00:37:26,752 --> 00:37:28,935
I was so happy being Gerry Hanscom.

576
00:37:30,166 --> 00:37:31,918
It was like being born again...

577
00:37:33,093 --> 00:37:35,201
like being present for my own birth.

578
00:37:36,231 --> 00:37:38,847
I don't understand.
So this guy gives people...

579
00:37:39,293 --> 00:37:40,250
new lives?

580
00:37:42,201 --> 00:37:44,741
But what if you're not in a natural disaster?

581
00:37:46,243 --> 00:37:48,134
How do you get the death certificate?

582
00:37:48,185 --> 00:37:51,799
For another $100,000, Sammy could tell you how to handle that, too.

583
00:37:51,857 --> 00:37:56,432
All you need is a year, a box of hypodermic needles and a portable freezer.

584
00:37:56,969 --> 00:37:58,033
What do you mean?

585
00:37:58,996 --> 00:38:01,578
He'd teach you how to collect your own blood--

586
00:38:01,757 --> 00:38:04,171
a pint or so every week or two.
Store it.

587
00:38:04,270 --> 00:38:05,330
Keep it cold.

588
00:38:05,826 --> 00:38:10,489
When you figured out where you want to die, dump the blood and make a real mess.

589
00:38:11,434 --> 00:38:13,685
There isn't a coroner anywhere

590
00:38:14,222 --> 00:38:18,364
who won't declare you legally dead if he sees at least four liters of blood.

591
00:38:18,990 --> 00:38:20,301
Four liters, huh?

592
00:38:20,928 --> 00:38:22,915
Four liters is the magic number.

593
00:38:25,317 --> 00:38:26,943
And you worked for this guy?

594
00:38:27,144 --> 00:38:27,756
Yeah.

595
00:38:29,265 --> 00:38:29,912
Why?

596
00:38:30,307 --> 00:38:33,899
Because I need you to do me a favor.

597
00:38:39,226 --> 00:38:39,952
Cynthia?

598
00:38:42,406 --> 00:38:43,164
Maybe.

599
00:38:46,510 --> 00:38:47,658
You work for Sammy?

600
00:38:49,506 --> 00:38:50,696
Are those my papers?

601
00:38:50,954 --> 00:38:52,446
My name is Allison Dubois.

602
00:38:54,587 --> 00:38:59,015
I work for the Phoenix District Attorney's Office, and, yeah, these are your papers.

603
00:38:59,295 --> 00:38:59,933
Unfortunately,

604
00:38:59,984 --> 00:39:03,916
I'm going to need to hang onto these as evidence in a trial against you

605
00:39:04,173 --> 00:39:06,293
on charges of blackmail and fraud.

606
00:39:13,129 --> 00:39:14,671
Did you do it by yourself?

607
00:39:17,006 --> 00:39:18,279
Pretty much.

608
00:39:20,085 --> 00:39:20,823
I, uh...

609
00:39:22,209 --> 00:39:25,769
I paid a vagrant ten dollars to put the disc in the case at the video store,

610
00:39:25,820 --> 00:39:30,247
and I hired another guy for 20 to make the phone call to my dad.

611
00:39:34,177 --> 00:39:37,757
If you're working for my father, you're in league with the devil.

612
00:39:39,218 --> 00:39:40,970
So long as you understand that.

613
00:39:41,870 --> 00:39:43,741
I have a pretty good idea...

614
00:39:44,602 --> 00:39:45,976
of what he did to you.

615
00:39:48,986 --> 00:39:50,796
You don't know the half of it.

616
00:39:56,343 --> 00:39:57,701
Pretty screwed-up world.

617
00:39:58,699 --> 00:40:00,416
After everything that he did,

618
00:40:01,908 --> 00:40:04,435
I'll rot in a jail cell, and he'll be walking free.

619
00:40:04,486 --> 00:40:07,438
Not necessarily.
He said that there was some recording.

620
00:40:08,060 --> 00:40:11,556
- If we could get our hands on that...
- I was 19 on that DVD.

621
00:40:13,784 --> 00:40:16,140
He'll argue that there was implied consent.

622
00:40:21,416 --> 00:40:27,492
Unfortunately, I wasn't smart enough to tape us when I was 11...

623
00:40:29,100 --> 00:40:30,445
or 12 or...

624
00:40:41,790 --> 00:40:45,094
Hang onto these papers, Elizabeth.
You're going to need them.

625
00:40:48,135 --> 00:40:50,365
I'm sorry I bothered you.

626
00:40:50,416 --> 00:40:52,898
I thought you were someone else, another girl.

627
00:40:54,216 --> 00:40:58,522
I heard she was dead, but when I saw you, I thought maybe.

628
00:41:02,215 --> 00:41:03,747
I guess I was wrong.

629
00:41:05,722 --> 00:41:07,540
How far are we from the border here?

630
00:41:07,591 --> 00:41:08,744
Half a mile?

631
00:41:10,123 --> 00:41:13,669
With the right papers, a person could safely get across the border in 15 minutes,

632
00:41:13,720 --> 00:41:18,042
so even if a person did mistakenly spot you and happen to call the authorities,

633
00:41:18,168 --> 00:41:20,865
you could be safely gone before they arrived.

634
00:41:21,808 --> 00:41:22,542
Go.

635
00:41:23,003 --> 00:41:24,179
I got the check.

636
00:41:33,630 --> 00:41:36,120
You make sure that the right people see that.

637
00:41:37,943 --> 00:41:39,033
The girl on it...

638
00:41:40,837 --> 00:41:41,806
she's dead...

639
00:41:42,371 --> 00:41:43,259
but the man...

640
00:41:47,098 --> 00:41:47,968
Don't worry.

641
00:41:49,117 --> 00:41:50,793
I know what to do with this.

642
00:42:00,581 --> 00:42:01,303
Coffee?

643
00:42:01,354 --> 00:42:03,721
No, I'm fine.
Just-just the check.

644
00:42:04,351 --> 00:42:06,913
Hopefully everything met your expectations.

645
00:42:09,557 --> 00:42:10,345
Oh, yeah.

646
00:42:13,434 --> 00:42:15,130
Everything was perfect.

647
00:42:34,363 --> 00:42:37,331
